Lesson 1.3 - Defining community

---------- [L1]

RSS feed link: https://rss.com/podcasts/footnerdprogram/366099/

Video link: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZWiNKoSXIH4

Creators: Ruth & Nick

Framework:

- Defining community for yourself (note it in your log)
- Community nutrients
- Layers of community
- Learning pods
- Learning partners
- How we use Slack
- How we use Github

Audio lesson notes:
- detailed notes and timestamps from the audio lesson


Experiments (nano to macro)

- Define community for yourself (write in log)
- Ask close friends/family how they define community
- reflection: How do I currently get my community nutrients?
- List your layers of community in a visual diagram
- Start a conversation with a stranger in your local community
- Organize a community health discussion

